Let's find $f'(x)$:

$f'(x)=5\cdot \dfrac{1}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}$

Now let's evaluate $f'\left(\dfrac{2}{3}\right)$:

$\begin{align}f'\left(\dfrac{2}{3}\right)&=5\cdot \dfrac{1}{\sqrt{1-\left(\dfrac23\right)^2}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{5}{\sqrt{\dfrac{5}{9}}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{5}{\left(\dfrac{\sqrt{5}}{3}\right)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{15}{\sqrt{5}}
\\\\
&=3\sqrt{5}\end{align}$

Let's find $f'(x)$:

$f'(x)=3\cdot \dfrac{-1}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}$

Now let's evaluate $f'\left(\dfrac{1}{2}\right)$:

$\begin{align}f'\left(\dfrac{1}{2}\right)&=3\cdot \dfrac{-1}{\sqrt{1-\left(\dfrac12\right)^2}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-3}{\sqrt{\dfrac{3}{4}}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-3}{\left(\dfrac{\sqrt{3}}{2}\right)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-6}{\sqrt{3}}
\\\\
&=-2\sqrt{3}\end{align}$
